#
# DFT umbrella-sampling window @ d_FeH = 2.25 A (KineticTrap mackinawite Fe-H trap)
# DRAFT s167 2026-06-11 -- PENDING /test (opus) + consilium on CV-match & K-units.
# Backbone from W2 grotthuss_metadyn.inp (s121) with CUTOFF 320->600 (s164 convergence).
# System: 3x3x1 mackinawite Fe18S18 + 12 H2O + 1 excess H = 73 atoms, charge +1, nspin=1 (RKS PM surrogate).
# CV = DISTANCE(excess-H atom 38, chemisorption Fe 13) -- matches MLIP smooth-min(d_FeH) in the trap region.
# Restraint: apples-to-apples with MLIP US (kappa=1000 kJ/mol/A^2, V=0.5*kappa*d^2).
#   CP2K RESTRAINT energy = K*(X-TARGET)^2 -- NO 1/2 factor (verified CP2K manual, consilium s167).
#   => to match MLIP physical stiffness: K_CP2K = 0.5*kappa = 500 kJ/mol/A^2 = 140.0 kJ/mol/Bohr^2
#   (Bohr-based: CP2K colvar distance is internal Bohr; 500*0.28003=140.0). Set `K [kjmol] 140.0`.
#   ## /test ITEM #1: smoke sigma(xi) = sqrt(kT/(2*K)) ~ 0.0499 A (NOTE: /(2K) because no 1/2 in E).
#      If smoke sigma ~0.035 A -> K is 2x too stiff (old 280.1 bug); if ~0.07 -> 2x too soft.
# To make the other windows: copy this file, change TARGET [angstrom] to 1.90 / 2.40, and PROJECT name.
# Windows >2.6 A: add an upper WALL at 3.0 A (thin-cell honest target d_FeH<=3.0).
#
&GLOBAL
  PROJECT smoke_2p40
  RUN_TYPE MD
  PRINT_LEVEL LOW
  WALLTIME -1
  PREFERRED_DIAG_LIBRARY SCALAPACK
  &FM
    TYPE_OF_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION SCALAPACK
  &END FM
&END GLOBAL

&FORCE_EVAL
  METHOD Quickstep
  &DFT
    BASIS_SET_FILE_NAME BASIS_MOLOPT
    POTENTIAL_FILE_NAME GTH_POTENTIALS
    CHARGE 1
    &QS
      EPS_DEFAULT 1.0E-12
      EXTRAPOLATION ASPC
      EXTRAPOLATION_ORDER 3
    &END QS
    &MGRID
      CUTOFF 600
      REL_CUTOFF 60
      NGRIDS 4
    &END MGRID
    &XC
      &XC_FUNCTIONAL PBE
      &END XC_FUNCTIONAL
      &VDW_POTENTIAL
        POTENTIAL_TYPE PAIR_POTENTIAL
        &PAIR_POTENTIAL
          TYPE DFTD3(BJ)
          REFERENCE_FUNCTIONAL PBE
        &END PAIR_POTENTIAL
      &END VDW_POTENTIAL
    &END XC
    &SCF
      SCF_GUESS ATOMIC
      MAX_SCF 300
      EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
      ADDED_MOS 64
      &DIAGONALIZATION
        ALGORITHM STANDARD
      &END DIAGONALIZATION
      &MIXING
        METHOD BROYDEN_MIXING
        ALPHA 0.2
        NBROYDEN 8
      &END MIXING
      &SMEAR
        METHOD FERMI_DIRAC
        ELECTRONIC_TEMPERATURE [K] 500
      &END SMEAR
      &OUTER_SCF
        EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
        MAX_SCF 10
      &END OUTER_SCF
    &END SCF
  &END DFT

  &SUBSYS
    &CELL
      A  11.022  0.000  0.000
      B   0.000 11.022  0.000
      C   0.000  0.000  6.500
      PERIODIC XYZ
    &END CELL
    &TOPOLOGY
      COORD_FILE_NAME w2_frame0.xyz
      COORD_FILE_FORMAT XYZ
    &END TOPOLOGY
    &COLVAR
      &DISTANCE
        ATOMS 38 13
      &END DISTANCE
    &END COLVAR
    &KIND Fe
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q16
    &END KIND
    &KIND S
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND O
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND H
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q1
    &END KIND
  &END SUBSYS
&END FORCE_EVAL

&MOTION
  &MD
    ENSEMBLE NVT
    STEPS 400
    TIMESTEP [fs] 0.5
    TEMPERATURE [K] 300.0
    &THERMOSTAT
      TYPE NOSE
      REGION GLOBAL
      &NOSE
        LENGTH 3
        TIMECON [fs] 500.0
        MTS 2
      &END NOSE
    &END THERMOSTAT
  &END MD

  &CONSTRAINT
    &COLLECTIVE
      COLVAR 1
      INTERMOLECULAR T
      TARGET [angstrom] 2.40
      &RESTRAINT
        K [kjmol] 140.0
      &END RESTRAINT
    &END COLLECTIVE
  &END CONSTRAINT

  &PRINT
    &TRAJECTORY
      &EACH
        MD 2
      &END EACH
      FORMAT XYZ
    &END TRAJECTORY
    &RESTART
      &EACH
        MD 50
      &END EACH
      BACKUP_COPIES 1
    &END RESTART
  &END PRINT
&END MOTION

# COLVAR value is printed by the &CONSTRAINT machinery to PROJECT-1.restraint / .LagrangeMultLog;
# the carrier-decisive observables (d(38,13) + nearest d_SH + nearest d_OH of atom 38) are
# post-processed from the printed trajectory. (No hills / no bias-deposition here -- this is a
# restrained-MD umbrella window, not metadynamics.)
# NOTE: GPW (not GAPW) is the VALIDATED project backbone -- GTH pseudopotentials are GPW-designed
# (CP2K_SHARED_BACKBONE.md line 10, s164 cross-plane). The lint C-4 GAPW WARN is a known accepted
# deviation; do NOT switch to GAPW (breaks comparability with the validated cross-plane backbone).
